				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$H^1$$\end{document}H1 seminorm to estimate the error [1]. Apart from the element interior residual, the flux jumps across the inter-element edges influence the element error. The flux jump of each edge is computed and added to the element error contribution. For both the element residual and flux jump, the values of the desired variables at each node are necessary. Therefore, the error \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
